Executive Profile
Patricia A. Gottesman  Independent Director, World Wrestling Entertainment, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships58$128,041
Background

		Ms. Patricia A. Gottesman was Founder and Principal for Omnibus PG. Ms. Gottesman serves as the Chairman of the Advisory Board of Ninah, the global management and analytics consulting unit of the Paris-based Publicis Groupe. Ms. Gottesman serves in advisory roles for TechMahindra. Ms. Gottesman is a C-suite Executive with expertise in digital media, analytics, marketing, operations and new product development. Ms. Gottesman served as the Chief Executive Officer and President ... of Crimson Hexagon, Inc. from 2011 to 2012. Prior to Crimson Hexagon, she held top P&L roles in product, marketing and brand strategy, business and operations at Cablevision Systems Corporation. She served as an Executive Vice President of Product Management of Cablevision Systems Corporation since January 2005 and also served as its Executive Vice President of Marketing, Digital Marketing & Commerce. She was responsible for Marketing all of Cablevision's telecommunications products. She led Cablevision Systems Corp. (NYSE: CVC) new Digital Marketing & Commerce group. Ms. Gottesman served as Senior Product Development and Marketing Executive of Cablevision Systems Corp. for more than a decade. She served with Cablevision for 29 years and served as its Senior Vice President of Marketing. She served as Senior Vice President of Development at Cablevision Systems Corporation. She served as a Director of Rentrak Corporation since August 13, 2014. She has been a Director of Crimson Hexagon, Inc. since December 2010. She has been an Independent Director at World Wrestling Entertainment Inc. since June 2011. She serves on the Board of Directors of WWE. She has been a Member of Board of Advisors at Razorsight Corporation since March 4, 2014. She serves as a Member of the Board of Advisors at Elucido Media Networks Pvt. Ltd. She served as a Director at comScore, Inc. since December 23, 2015. Ms. Gottesman serves in advisory roles for America India Foundation. She is a Trustee for the Washington-based Committee for Economic Development (CED). She received the NCTA Vanguard Award; shared responsibility with the operating team for delivering a $6 billion annual consumer and SMB revenue budget; led the 120-member branding, marketing and product teams that developed and executed the cable industry’s Optimum branding and Triple Play acquisition strategy; was one of three inventors on an ad-tech cable patent;  and led the brand and product teams that won two NATAS Emmy Awards for digital interactive television. Ms. Gottesman graduated magna cum laude from Hofstra University with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Communications.Read Full Background




