Management
Patricia Gottesman








Patricia GottesmanFormer CEO, Crimson Hexagon & Chair, Advisory Board, Ninah/PublicisPatricia Gottesman is a C-suite executive with expertise in digital media, analytics, marketing, operations and new product development.In addition to comScore, Ms. Gottesman serves on the Board of Directors of WWE (NYSE: WWE), a leading global sports entertainment company and has previously served on the Board of Directors of Rentrak and as a Trustee for the DC-based Committee for Economic Development. She currently chairs the Advisory Board of Ninah, a strategic consulting unit of the Paris-based Publicis Groupe.In 2011 and 2012, Ms. Gottesman served as President and CEO of Harvard University SaaS analytics start-up Crimson Hexagon. Ms. Gottesman and her team brought a significant funding round into the company, delivering the foundation for unparalleled growth. During this period, Crimson Hexagon was recognized as number seven on “Fast Company’s” list of "The 10 Most Innovative Companies on the Web" (March 2011), quadrupled its global client base and secured a Fortune 500 top client list with an average market cap of more than $7 billion.Prior to Crimson Hexagon, Ms. Gottesman held top P&L roles in product, marketing and brand strategy, business and operations at Cablevision—the fifth largest U.S. cable distributor, MSG owner and the creator of AMC Networks. She received the NCTA Vanguard Award; shared responsibility with the operating team for delivering a $6 billion annual consumer and SMB revenue budget; led the 120-member branding, marketing and product teams that developed and executed the cable industry’s Optimum branding and Triple Play acquisition strategy; was one of three inventors on an ad-tech cable patent; and, led the brand and product teams that won two NATAS Emmy Awards for digital interactive television.












